(Note: in case you're wondering, Telescope is an open-source social news app built with the [Meteor](http://www.meteor.com) JavaScript framework. Think [Hacker News](http://news.ycombinator.com) or [Reddit](http://reddit.com), but responsive, modern, and real-time!)


### Introducing IronRouter

The biggest change is the switch to [IronRouter](https://github.com/EventedMind/iron-router), the new Router package developed by Chris Mather and Tom Coleman. 

![https://github.com/EventedMind/iron-router](http://f.cl.ly/items/2Y2p0q3C0a3E3W3w2E1z/iron.png)

IronRouter was made from scratch with Meteor apps in mind, and apart from its routing features it also helps a lot when it comes to subscriptions.

Now, instead of throwing in all your subscription code in your `main.js` file and hoping for the best, IronRouter will let you specify which subscriptions to load on which route, and whether or not to wait for them.

### In Progress

This means you can now do really cool things such as use the [nProgress](http://ricostacruz.com/nprogress/) JavaScript plugin (there's also a [Meteorite package](https://atmosphere.meteor.com/package/nprogress)) to display a Medium-style progress bar between each page. 

